960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_PDP508.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></section><p data-caps="initial" class="article__body-text article__body-text--dropcap">天使之城<span data-caps="initial">完美</span><small>的</small>气候和蓬勃发展的经济吸引了一代又一代的加州梦想家。但现在<a href="https://www.economist.com/united-states/2023/08/17/the-hollywood-strikes-reveal-los-angeless-deepest-anxieties">美国第二大城市正在变得越来越小</a>——人口和企业都在流失。正如<a href="https://www.economist.com/podcasts/2023/07/27/why-is-hollywood-on-strike">好莱坞罢工所揭示的</a>那样，住房、生活和经营企业的高昂成本正在将洛杉矶人赶走。这座城市能否扭转大收缩的局面？但洛杉矶变小还有问题吗？</p><p class="article__body-text">该市市长凯伦·巴斯和一名纠察演员阐述了该市面临的负担能力问题，而洛杉矶县经济发展公司的香农·塞奇威克则解释了商业外流背后的原因。我们回顾了这座城市过去的繁荣岁月，加州公共政策研究所的汉斯·约翰逊探讨了如何让它们回归。</p><p class="article__body-text">约翰·普里多 (John Prideaux) 与夏洛特·霍华德 (Charlotte Howard) 和伊德里斯·卡隆 (Idrees Kahloon) 共同主持。</p><p class="article__body-text">时长：45分钟</p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="215" src="https://embed.acast.com/checksandbalance/checks-and-balance-los-diablos-de-los-angeles" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">现在，您可以<a href="https://www.economist.com/checkspod" data-tegid="d0fgcd8nh46pfpoj91eiou25fqf2uodg">在一个地方</a>找到《制衡》的每一集，并订阅我们的每周时事<a href="https://www.economist.com/newsletters">通讯</a>。如需完全访问印刷版、数字版和音频版以及独家现场活动，请通过<a href="http://economist.com/USpod">coneconomicist.com/uspod</a>订阅<i>《经济学人》</i> 。</p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 01 Sep 2023 15:48:57 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/66tu3rvn5sc32cr0j3fkgl1fhikni0pd</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/podcasts/2023/09/01/falling-population-rising-costs-what-is-bedevilling-the-city-of-angels</item></channel></rss>